Goal
Build and maintain a multi-agent AI system (SwarmMind) as Lane 3 in a 4-lane lattice (Archivist, Library, SwarmMind, Kernel) that communicates via a file-based lane-relay protocol. The system enforces strict governance, attestation, and verification across lanes. SwarmMind's role is trace-mediated verification surface (Position 3, Authority 80, can_govern: false).
Instructions
- Lane-Relay Protocol is ENFORCED: All cross-lane communication uses lanes/{lane}/inbox/ structure. Read inbox first, process by priority (P0>P1>P2>P3), move to processed/, log to outbox/.
- Git Protocol is MANDATORY: Commit + push as ONE action. Never leave commits local-only. Verify push success.
- Canonical Paths are P0: Senders MUST write to the target lane's OWN repo, not their local mirror copy. This was the biggest bug discovered.
- Fail-closed behavior: Constructor hard-rejects legacy options. Missing enforcement modules cause process.exit(1). No silent degradation.
- SwarmMind Identity: Position 3, Authority 80, Role: trace-mediated-verification-surface, can_govern: false. Cannot modify governance files (requires authority 100).
- Worker Contract (v1.0): ACQUIRE → EXECUTE → EVIDENCE → REPORT → HEARTBEAT. All messages must include schema_version, task_id, idempotency_key, lease, retry, evidence, heartbeat fields.
- Codex v1.1 Schema Patch: All 4 items approved (canonical paths, payload indirection, execution provenance, watcher policy block). Awaiting formal ratification from Archivist.
- Lane 4 (Kernel-Lane): Position 4, Authority 70, can_govern: false, Role: gpu-optimized-artifact-generation. Canonical path: S:/kernel-lane/lanes/kernel/inbox/. lane_id = kernel (not kernel-lane).
- Rate Limiting: ONE heartbeat file per lane (overwrite in place), max 60s between writes. No UUID-named temp files.
- Cross-lane delivery verification: node scripts/verify-delivery.js must show 0 mirror-only, 0 missing before declaring any phase complete.
